The African National Congress in Gauteng will give an update about its action to intervene in the widely reported allegations of the PPE procurement process within the Gauteng Department of Health. Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above.  JOHANNESBURG - The ANC is giving an update on the probe into the R125-million PPE tender scandal. Senior officials are linked to the tender including the President’s Spokesperson Khusela Diko, and Gauteng Health MEC Bandile Masuku. READ: ANC to give update on controversial PPE tender The Gauteng ANC held a special Provincial Executive Committee following the allegations. The PEC will give an update on the decisions of the Special PEC.